    <subfield code="y">00012 (Left Panel) The intersection of the two solid lines shows the black hole mass and spin for the source GRO~J1655$-$40 for which the observed 300~Hz and the 450~Hz oscillations can be explained as the lowest order $c$- and $g$-modes, respectively. The intersection of the dotted lines makes the opposite identification of disk modes to the observed oscillatory frequencies (after~\cite{Wagoner01}). (Right Panel) Each solid line traces pairs of black hole mass and spin for which the observed frequencies correspond to different resonances between the Keplerian and periastron precession frequencies (after~\cite{Abramowicz02}). In both panels, the horizontal dashed lines show the uncertainty in the dynamically measured mass of theblack hole.</subfield>
  </datafield>
